# References

Below are some references to highlight based on the slides and code:

* [The PRECIS-2 tool: designing trials that are fit for purpose](https://doi.org/10.1136/bmj.h2147): the BMJ paper introducing the PRECIS-2 framework that helps to summarize how trials may be made pragmatic on different elements

* [CONSORT 2010 statement](https://www.equator-network.org/reporting-guidelines/consort/): the CONSORT guidelines provide a template of what to report (and what we should be thinking of when designing a study)

